 direction $a$ and $b=na(\\beta)$\nis the blocked lattice spacing. Beautiful scaling behaviors are seen when we\nplot $\\rho(a(\\beta),n)$ versus $b=na(\\beta)$. A single universal curve\n$\\rho(b)$ is found from $n=1\\sim 12$, which suggests that $\\rho(a(\\beta),n)$ is\na function of $b=na(\\beta)$ alone. The universal curve seems independent of a\ngauge fixing procedure used to smooth the lattice vacuum when the scaling is\nobtained. The scaling shows that the lattice definition of VNABI has the\ncontinuum limit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 16 Dec 2017 11:47:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 May 2018 00:54:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-14"}
